1
00:00:03,216 --> 00:00:06,913
^^ [ Woman Vocalizing ]

2
00:00:10,257 --> 00:00:12,817
[ Man Narrating ]
Prevlously on The Bible.

3
00:00:12,893 --> 00:00:16,192
Human failings led to the great flood.

4
00:00:16,263 --> 00:00:18,731
Wrong choices, wrong decisions.

5
00:00:18,799 --> 00:00:21,859
[ Narrator ]
After Noah, a new beginning...

6
00:00:21,935 --> 00:00:24,563
and a promise for Abraham.

7
00:00:24,638 --> 00:00:26,538
God has spoken to me.

8
00:00:26,606 --> 00:00:30,064
He will lead us to a new home.

9
00:00:30,143 --> 00:00:34,136
He has promised descendants
as numerous as the stars.

10
00:00:34,214 --> 00:00:37,081
[ Narrator ]
To help the Israelites fulfill the promise...

11
00:00:37,150 --> 00:00:40,449
God sent Moses to free them from slavery.

12
00:00:40,520 --> 00:00:42,283
Lord!

13
00:00:44,157 --> 00:00:48,025
Joshua led them into the promised land.

14
00:00:48,095 --> 00:00:51,394
Jericho is ours!
[ Shouts ]

15
00:00:51,465 --> 00:00:52,625
[ All Shouting ]

16
00:00:52,699 --> 00:00:54,633
[ Chanting ]
lsrael! lsrael!

17
00:00:54,701 --> 00:00:57,431
[ Narrator ]
But the Israelites faced brutal opposltlon...

18
00:00:57,504 --> 00:00:58,971
from the Philistines.

19
00:01:04,845 --> 00:01:06,938
Some dared to fight back.

20
00:01:07,881 --> 00:01:09,906
- [ Groans ]
- [ Shouts ]

21
00:01:11,351 --> 00:01:13,376
[ Grunting ]

22
00:01:13,453 --> 00:01:15,444
[ People Screaming ]

23
00:01:18,959 --> 00:01:22,258
But not even Samson could overcome them.

24
00:01:22,329 --> 00:01:27,062
The prophet SamueI
led the Israelites in God's name...

25
00:01:27,134 --> 00:01:29,568
but the people wanted more-

26
00:01:29,636 --> 00:01:31,797
someone to lead them in battle .

27
00:01:31,872 --> 00:01:33,567
- What do you want?
- A king.

28
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:36,438
A king? They become tyrants.

29
00:01:36,510 --> 00:01:38,774
[ Phineas ]
Not lf they are chosen by God.

30
00:01:38,845 --> 00:01:45,011
Saul, l anoint you
the first king of lsrael.

31
00:01:45,085 --> 00:01:48,748
May l, as God's prophet...

32
00:01:48,822 --> 00:01:51,484
help you in any way l can.

33
00:01:51,558 --> 00:01:56,655
[ Narrator ] But is any man good enough
to rule God's kingdom?

34
00:02:01,601 --> 00:02:04,798
[ Horses Whinny ln Distance ]

35
00:02:09,176 --> 00:02:10,768
[ Saul ]
Are the men ready?

36
00:02:10,844 --> 00:02:12,175
They're ready.

37
00:02:14,448 --> 00:02:16,643
Where is Samuel?

38
00:02:16,716 --> 00:02:18,707
He should be here.

39
00:02:20,053 --> 00:02:22,886
We must make a sacrifice before we attack.

40
00:02:26,593 --> 00:02:28,390
We cannot wait any longer.

41
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,395
[ Bleating ]

42
00:02:35,469 --> 00:02:37,562
[ Samuel ]
Saul! May God forgive you!

43
00:02:37,637 --> 00:02:39,332
Samuel.

44
00:02:39,406 --> 00:02:40,873
Where were you?

45
00:02:40,941 --> 00:02:44,206
Seven days we have waited. Seven days.

46
00:02:44,277 --> 00:02:45,767
My men are deserting.

47
00:02:45,846 --> 00:02:49,680
Then be a king.
Leave the job of priest to me.

48
00:02:49,749 --> 00:02:52,582
Do you think God values
your sacrifice more than mine?

49
00:02:52,652 --> 00:02:54,142
Samuel.

50
00:02:55,856 --> 00:02:57,881
God instructs you-

51
00:02:57,958 --> 00:02:59,550
kill everyone...

52
00:02:59,626 --> 00:03:01,719
and everything.

53
00:03:14,841 --> 00:03:18,675
[ Narrator ]
A new era in Israelite history is beginning-

54
00:03:18,745 --> 00:03:21,976
the perlod of prophets and kings.

55
00:03:23,817 --> 00:03:28,083
They must work together
to secure the promised land.

56
00:03:32,125 --> 00:03:34,059
[ Horse Whinnying ]

57
00:03:35,462 --> 00:03:37,430
- [ Groans ]
- [ Man ] To arms!

58
00:03:50,477 --> 00:03:51,535
[ Screaming ]

59
00:04:00,186 --> 00:04:02,154
[ Man ]
Victory!

60
00:04:11,431 --> 00:04:14,332
[ Men Chanting ]
Saul! Saul! Saul!

61
00:04:14,401 --> 00:04:16,426
Saul! Saul! Saul!

62
00:04:16,503 --> 00:04:18,403
God is with me!

63
00:04:18,471 --> 00:04:20,496
- God is with me!
- [ Cheering ]

64
00:04:24,678 --> 00:04:26,339
You had one task...

65
00:04:26,413 --> 00:04:28,472
one simple command from God.

66
00:04:28,548 --> 00:04:32,177
- Destroy everything.
- We followed his commands.

67
00:04:32,252 --> 00:04:34,880
Then what is this bleating
of goats in my ears?

68
00:04:34,955 --> 00:04:38,584
What is this lowing of cattle
and wailing of lambs?

69
00:04:38,658 --> 00:04:41,593
- Can the dead cry out?
- [ Laughing ]

70
00:04:41,661 --> 00:04:43,754
And who is this pagan king?

71
00:04:43,830 --> 00:04:46,765
[ Saul ]
He is to be put to death later.

72
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:50,064
When the Lord says spare, you spare.

73
00:04:50,136 --> 00:04:52,263
When he says kill-

74
00:04:52,339 --> 00:04:53,431
- [ Knife Plunges ]
- [ Groans ]

75
00:04:53,506 --> 00:04:54,996
Samuel!

76
00:04:57,544 --> 00:05:01,605
You are our prophet, but l am your king.

77
00:05:01,681 --> 00:05:04,650
What the Lord gives, he can take away.

78
00:05:04,718 --> 00:05:06,618
Are these God's words or yours?

79
00:05:06,686 --> 00:05:10,645
Your descendants could have ruled
for over a thousand years.

80
00:05:13,293 --> 00:05:15,454
But today...

81
00:05:15,528 --> 00:05:17,496
God has forsaken you.

82
00:05:18,198 --> 00:05:20,632
More divine words?

83
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:22,224
[ Cloth Rips ]

84
00:05:24,871 --> 00:05:27,738
God has torn your power from you.

85
00:05:29,209 --> 00:05:32,007
He wants a man after his own heart.

86
00:05:51,998 --> 00:05:54,330
- Bring me wine.
- Sire.

87
00:05:56,970 --> 00:05:59,063
Do you hear me? Now!

88
00:05:59,139 --> 00:06:00,629
Yes, sire!

89
00:06:03,576 --> 00:06:05,806
Perhaps l have been hasty.

90
00:06:08,181 --> 00:06:10,809
l should ask Samuel's forgiveness.

91
00:06:12,419 --> 00:06:16,014
- [ Liquid Pouring ]
- Bring Samuel to me.

92
00:06:16,089 --> 00:06:18,057
He's gone, Majesty.

93
00:06:19,626 --> 00:06:21,116
Gone?

94
00:06:26,199 --> 00:06:28,167
Samuel!

95
00:06:42,615 --> 00:06:44,344
[ Bleating ]

96
00:06:48,121 --> 00:06:50,214
[ Narrator ]
After Saulls disobedlence...

97
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:53,487
God commands his prophet Samuel...

98
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,721
to find a new king.

99
00:06:55,795 --> 00:06:57,990
- [ Snarling ]
- [ Bleating ]

100
00:06:58,064 --> 00:07:02,125
[ Snarling Continues ]

101
00:07:03,636 --> 00:07:07,231
[ Air Whlpping ]

102
00:07:07,307 --> 00:07:09,798
- [ Thud ]
- [ Yelping ]

103
00:07:10,477 --> 00:07:12,445
Young man!

104
00:07:14,647 --> 00:07:16,945
What is your name?

105
00:07:17,550 --> 00:07:19,245
David, sir.

106
00:07:20,220 --> 00:07:22,450
My name is David.

107
00:07:42,709 --> 00:07:45,701
l anoint you, David of Bethlehem...

108
00:07:45,779 --> 00:07:48,771
to be the next king of lsrael...

109
00:07:50,116 --> 00:07:52,243
once Saul is dead.

110
00:08:01,928 --> 00:08:03,589
Father, what's wrong?

111
00:08:05,265 --> 00:08:07,028
Tell me what's wrong.

112
00:08:08,635 --> 00:08:10,125
Nothing is wrong.

113
00:08:10,203 --> 00:08:12,000
lt was a great victory.

114
00:08:12,071 --> 00:08:16,007
l need rest. That is all.

115
00:08:17,544 --> 00:08:20,604
Sleep. Sleep.

116
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:24,172
Lord, forgive your servant!

117
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:25,615
[ Groans ]

118
00:08:27,587 --> 00:08:30,249
^^ [ Soothing ]

119
00:08:31,457 --> 00:08:32,947
[ Narrator ]
In time...

120
00:08:33,026 --> 00:08:36,291
Davld becomes an attendant
in Saulls court-

121
00:08:37,330 --> 00:08:39,696
a king in walting.

122
00:08:43,837 --> 00:08:45,361
[ Loud Clattering ]

123
00:08:47,340 --> 00:08:49,399
[ Clattering Continues ]

124
00:08:53,813 --> 00:08:57,613
The Philistine threat continues to grow.

125
00:08:57,684 --> 00:09:01,245
[ Thudding Footsteps ]

126
00:09:01,321 --> 00:09:04,085
Now they have a new champlon-

127
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:07,691
[ Footsteps Trampling ]

128
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,250
Goliath.

129
00:09:21,407 --> 00:09:23,637
Will one of you fight me?

130
00:09:23,710 --> 00:09:27,237
lsraelites, you win...

131
00:09:27,313 --> 00:09:30,771
and the Philistines will be your slaves.

132
00:09:30,850 --> 00:09:32,477
l win...

133
00:09:32,552 --> 00:09:34,577
and you...

134
00:09:34,654 --> 00:09:36,645
will be our slaves.

135
00:09:36,723 --> 00:09:39,214
- Someone must fight him!
- Not you, Jonathan.

136
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:44,753
The warrior who defeats him...
will be a rich man.

137
00:09:45,899 --> 00:09:48,891
[ Goliath ]
Not one man in lsrael?

138
00:09:50,303 --> 00:09:52,464
Not one of God's people.

139
00:09:56,743 --> 00:09:58,301
l'll do it.

140
00:09:59,646 --> 00:10:00,977
[ Quietly ]
David.

141
00:10:01,047 --> 00:10:03,311
You're no soldier. You're a shepherd.

142
00:10:03,383 --> 00:10:05,544
Yes, a shepherd.

143
00:10:09,088 --> 00:10:11,386
As l protect my sheep,
God will protect me.

144
00:10:11,457 --> 00:10:13,448
[ Goliath ]
Where is your faith?

145
00:10:13,526 --> 00:10:16,017
Where is your god?

146
00:10:17,664 --> 00:10:19,154
l will kill him.

147
00:10:20,266 --> 00:10:21,995
You'll need this.

148
00:10:34,547 --> 00:10:36,606
l'll be better without it.

149
00:10:39,552 --> 00:10:41,952
[ Shields Clattering ]

150
00:10:42,021 --> 00:10:46,151
Yea, though l walk in the valley
of the shadow of death...

151
00:10:47,527 --> 00:10:49,222
l fear no evil...

152
00:10:50,096 --> 00:10:52,155
for you are with me.

153
00:10:52,231 --> 00:10:53,721
Thy rod and staff...

154
00:10:55,101 --> 00:10:56,830
they comfort me.

155
00:10:57,870 --> 00:10:59,895
You anoint my head with oil.

156
00:11:01,407 --> 00:11:02,965
My cup overflows.

157
00:11:04,143 --> 00:11:06,907
Surely goodness and mercy
shall follow me...

158
00:11:07,947 --> 00:11:10,040
all the days of my life.

159
00:11:10,116 --> 00:11:12,414
[ Clattering Continues ]

160
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:20,725
[ Men Laughing ]

161
00:11:31,804 --> 00:11:33,237
[ Helmet Clatters ]

162
00:11:33,306 --> 00:11:35,536
lsrael has found a champion.

163
00:11:35,608 --> 00:11:39,772
[ Laughing ]

164
00:11:43,216 --> 00:11:44,706
[ Laughter Subsides ]

165
00:11:44,784 --> 00:11:47,082
Don't waste my time, little boy.

166
00:11:47,153 --> 00:11:49,178
You're too young to die.

167
00:11:52,325 --> 00:11:54,350
l will fight you.

168
00:12:19,919 --> 00:12:21,250
[ Groans ]

169
00:12:23,356 --> 00:12:25,290
[ Cheering ]

170
00:12:25,358 --> 00:12:28,623
Father, he did it.
David did it.

171
00:12:32,665 --> 00:12:34,360
[ Grunts ]

172
00:12:39,972 --> 00:12:42,338
[ Shouting ]

173
00:12:42,408 --> 00:12:45,400
Let us make slaves of them!

174
00:12:55,488 --> 00:12:56,716
David!

175
00:12:57,623 --> 00:12:59,921
My wolf in shepherd's clothing.

176
00:12:59,992 --> 00:13:03,223
You've saved my kingdom,
my shepherd warrior!

177
00:13:03,896 --> 00:13:05,523
Come with me, brother.

178
00:13:15,108 --> 00:13:16,632
[ Groans ]

179
00:13:16,709 --> 00:13:19,678
[ Narrator ]
Davld joins Saulls army...

180
00:13:19,745 --> 00:13:22,407
and battles the Philistines for decades.

181
00:13:32,558 --> 00:13:34,321
He becomes a warrlor...

182
00:13:35,928 --> 00:13:37,452
a leader...

183
00:13:39,298 --> 00:13:40,788
a hero.

184
00:13:42,969 --> 00:13:46,302
[ People Chanting ]
Saul! Saul! Saul!

185
00:13:46,372 --> 00:13:49,136
Saul! Saul! Saul!

186
00:13:49,208 --> 00:13:52,041
[ Man ]
Saul has killed thousands!

187
00:13:52,111 --> 00:13:55,979
Saul! Saul! Saul!

188
00:13:56,048 --> 00:13:57,413
Saul! Saul!

189
00:13:57,483 --> 00:14:00,247
Saul! Saul! Saul!

190
00:14:00,319 --> 00:14:02,617
You hear that, Father?

191
00:14:02,688 --> 00:14:04,349
l hear.

192
00:14:04,423 --> 00:14:06,152
[ Chanting Continues ]
Saul! Saul!

193
00:14:06,225 --> 00:14:09,786
Saul! Saul! Saul!

194
00:14:09,862 --> 00:14:11,261
[ Cheering Grows Louder ]

195
00:14:11,330 --> 00:14:14,299
[ Man ]
David has killed tens of thousands!

196
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:15,994
[ People Chanting ]
David! David!

197
00:14:16,068 --> 00:14:18,502
David! David!

198
00:14:18,571 --> 00:14:20,334
David! David!

199
00:14:20,406 --> 00:14:23,273
David! David! David!

200
00:14:23,342 --> 00:14:26,709
- David! David!
- He deserves their praise.

201
00:14:26,779 --> 00:14:29,077
He'll want my crown next.

202
00:14:29,148 --> 00:14:31,742
David! David!

203
00:14:31,817 --> 00:14:34,183
David! David!

204
00:14:36,622 --> 00:14:39,989
[ Jonathan Chattering ]

205
00:14:41,527 --> 00:14:43,518
[ David ] l thought you were going
to fall off your horse.

206
00:14:43,596 --> 00:14:45,257
[ Jonathan ]
l did fall off my horse.

207
00:14:45,331 --> 00:14:47,356
l think l killed a man
when l landed on him.

208
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:50,061
There was one point,
there were two men in front of me.

209
00:14:50,136 --> 00:14:52,400
David.

210
00:14:56,409 --> 00:14:57,899
Come here.

211
00:15:03,349 --> 00:15:04,941
So...

212
00:15:07,486 --> 00:15:10,819
once again, you are our champion.

213
00:15:13,359 --> 00:15:15,122
You have killed thousands.

214
00:15:15,194 --> 00:15:17,094
Tens of thousands.

215
00:15:17,163 --> 00:15:19,222
Of course.

216
00:15:19,298 --> 00:15:21,129
Tens of thousands.

217
00:15:23,736 --> 00:15:26,466
Our people are very grateful to you.

218
00:15:27,540 --> 00:15:29,565
The Lord blessed us all.

219
00:15:34,747 --> 00:15:37,079
l would like to reward you.

220
00:15:47,593 --> 00:15:50,824
l offer you my daughter, Michal.

221
00:15:56,969 --> 00:15:58,459
l'm very honored, Majesty.

222
00:16:00,706 --> 00:16:03,470
David, we're brothers now.

223
00:16:05,111 --> 00:16:06,772
[ Laughs ]

224
00:16:06,846 --> 00:16:09,110
ln return-

225
00:16:11,851 --> 00:16:14,149
100 dead Philistines.

226
00:16:14,987 --> 00:16:17,353
Hmm? What say you?

227
00:16:17,423 --> 00:16:21,792
100 dead Philistines
slain by your own hand.

228
00:16:21,861 --> 00:16:23,351
Father...

229
00:16:24,630 --> 00:16:26,621
he's risked his life enough, no?

230
00:16:26,699 --> 00:16:28,530
What if he doesn't return?

231
00:16:28,601 --> 00:16:30,091
l shall return.

232
00:16:33,306 --> 00:16:34,796
God willing.

233
00:17:06,172 --> 00:17:08,367
You love him like a brother, don't you?

234
00:17:09,442 --> 00:17:10,773
l do.

235
00:17:10,843 --> 00:17:14,404
[ Saul ]
As Abel, no doubt, once loved Cain.

236
00:17:15,881 --> 00:17:17,974
He wants our crown.

237
00:17:18,050 --> 00:17:21,110
- Can't you see?
- No.

238
00:17:21,187 --> 00:17:24,054
- He's loyal to us both.
- Nonsense!

239
00:17:32,098 --> 00:17:34,532
[ Footsteps Marching ]

240
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,227
[ Door Clanks ]

241
00:17:43,943 --> 00:17:46,104
[ David ]
A few mementos for you.

242
00:17:46,178 --> 00:17:48,373
And these.

243
00:17:50,116 --> 00:17:52,209
Trophies taken from each of their bodies.

244
00:17:54,220 --> 00:17:55,744
[ Flies Buzzing ]

245
00:17:58,157 --> 00:18:00,785
- [ Bag Thuds ]
- From a hundred men?

246
00:18:00,860 --> 00:18:02,691
200.

247
00:18:03,329 --> 00:18:04,921
God was with me.

248
00:18:07,466 --> 00:18:08,455
Michal.

249
00:18:19,178 --> 00:18:20,907
[ Michal ]
Let's go.

250
00:18:40,666 --> 00:18:41,792
[ Clatters ]

251
00:18:43,969 --> 00:18:46,938
Get out, all of you.

252
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,705
Get out!

253
00:18:58,851 --> 00:19:00,250
Father.

254
00:19:01,587 --> 00:19:04,317
What demons possess you?

255
00:19:04,390 --> 00:19:07,518
lf it wasn't for him,
we would all be slaves...

256
00:19:07,593 --> 00:19:09,584
and you would not be king.

257
00:19:09,662 --> 00:19:12,290
And with him, you never will be.

258
00:19:23,275 --> 00:19:26,073
Your father, the king,
wishes to see David.

259
00:19:26,946 --> 00:19:29,380
He can't. He's... not well.

260
00:19:30,916 --> 00:19:32,349
Not well!

261
00:19:34,854 --> 00:19:37,049
Not well, you say.

262
00:19:37,122 --> 00:19:40,990
Well- Well, we shall see.

263
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:43,028
We shall see.

264
00:19:43,863 --> 00:19:45,524
Not well.

265
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:49,227
- David?
- [ Pounds On Door ]

266
00:19:51,070 --> 00:19:52,298
Yes.

267
00:19:53,706 --> 00:19:55,640
Yes.

268
00:19:55,708 --> 00:19:57,335
Yes.

269
00:19:57,409 --> 00:20:00,435
You have helped him escape.

270
00:20:00,513 --> 00:20:04,779
- You would rather be queen
than see your own father king!
- No!

271
00:20:04,850 --> 00:20:07,080
You would betray your own brother!

272
00:20:07,152 --> 00:20:09,586
Father, you need to rest!

273
00:20:09,655 --> 00:20:13,955
So... even my own children
plot against me!

274
00:20:14,693 --> 00:20:16,558
David!

275
00:20:16,629 --> 00:20:18,859
David!

276
00:20:20,666 --> 00:20:25,933
Wherever you go, l shall hunt you down!

277
00:20:55,167 --> 00:20:56,691
Priests!

278
00:20:58,037 --> 00:21:00,505
Your king wishes to speak with you.

279
00:21:00,573 --> 00:21:02,438
[ Blusters ]

280
00:21:07,780 --> 00:21:09,975
- Come here! Out!
- Come on!

281
00:21:17,923 --> 00:21:19,914
David was here, wasn't he?

282
00:21:21,827 --> 00:21:24,694
- You sheltered him.
- [ Priest ] This is God's house.

283
00:21:25,664 --> 00:21:28,792
We offer shelter to all his people.

284
00:21:30,703 --> 00:21:32,034
Kill him.

285
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:37,637
l said kill him!

286
00:21:39,445 --> 00:21:41,208
[ Groaning ]

287
00:21:42,748 --> 00:21:44,272
Kill all of them.

288
00:21:45,117 --> 00:21:47,017
[ Groaning ]

289
00:22:18,117 --> 00:22:21,211
l have served you faithfully, Lord.

290
00:22:23,355 --> 00:22:25,550
As faithfully as a man can.

291
00:22:25,624 --> 00:22:28,422
And yet still it seems it is not enough.

292
00:22:28,494 --> 00:22:30,086
[ Echoing ]
Not enough.

293
00:22:30,162 --> 00:22:32,528
God is with me!

294
00:22:32,598 --> 00:22:34,566
[ Echoing ]
God is wlth me!

295
00:22:38,270 --> 00:22:40,067
Lord!

296
00:22:42,708 --> 00:22:46,405
[ Shouting ]
Do you hear your servant?

297
00:23:14,873 --> 00:23:17,933
[ Urinating ]

298
00:23:31,023 --> 00:23:32,854
[ Urinating Stops ]

299
00:23:37,563 --> 00:23:38,894
Majesty.

300
00:23:41,066 --> 00:23:42,795
David.

301
00:23:42,868 --> 00:23:45,962
Why do you pursue me
when l have done you no harm?

302
00:23:46,839 --> 00:23:48,773
l could have killed you.

303
00:23:50,142 --> 00:23:52,167
Your life was mine to take.

304
00:23:55,147 --> 00:23:57,308
Why didn't you take it then?

305
00:23:57,382 --> 00:23:59,714
The Lord may revenge
the harm you have done to me...

306
00:23:59,785 --> 00:24:01,810
but only evildoers do evil deeds.

307
00:24:01,887 --> 00:24:04,685
So my hand will not touch you. Ever.

308
00:24:04,757 --> 00:24:08,352
And God will reward you,
and you will be king!

309
00:24:08,427 --> 00:24:10,622
- You are my king.
- And when you have my crown...

310
00:24:10,696 --> 00:24:13,494
will you not kill my descendants,
bury my name?

311
00:24:13,565 --> 00:24:14,930
- l will not.
- No?

312
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,797
l swear.

313
00:24:18,303 --> 00:24:19,793
No?

314
00:24:20,806 --> 00:24:22,205
Come then.

315
00:24:23,142 --> 00:24:24,370
Come.

316
00:24:25,544 --> 00:24:27,341
We'll go home together.

317
00:24:52,171 --> 00:24:55,163
Why did you not kill him
when you had the chance?

318
00:24:57,276 --> 00:24:59,301
Because he's one of the anointed.

319
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:04,381
lt's up to God to decide his destiny.

320
00:25:07,452 --> 00:25:08,976
[ Jonathan ]
Father!

321
00:25:09,988 --> 00:25:11,012
Father!

322
00:25:11,089 --> 00:25:12,147
Father.

323
00:25:13,292 --> 00:25:14,725
Father.

324
00:25:14,793 --> 00:25:18,627
The Philistine army is in the next valley,
near Gilboa.

325
00:25:18,697 --> 00:25:22,258
Jonathan, David is very near.

326
00:25:22,334 --> 00:25:25,235
Forget about David.

327
00:25:26,572 --> 00:25:28,631
You must defend your kingdom.

328
00:25:28,707 --> 00:25:30,868
That is your duty.

329
00:25:35,581 --> 00:25:37,310
You're right.

330
00:25:38,884 --> 00:25:41,614
We must prepare for battle.

331
00:25:41,687 --> 00:25:44,918
Tell the men we leave for Gilboa.

332
00:25:44,990 --> 00:25:47,185
Tell them we leave at dawn.

333
00:25:49,428 --> 00:25:52,591
[ Shouting ]

334
00:25:56,602 --> 00:25:58,297
[ Shouts ]

335
00:26:00,472 --> 00:26:01,962
Jonathan, save yourself!

336
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:04,770
No! We stand together!

337
00:26:06,612 --> 00:26:09,308
Father, come on! Come on!

338
00:26:12,851 --> 00:26:14,341
[ Shouts ]

339
00:26:16,555 --> 00:26:18,147
[ Man ]
Draw!

340
00:26:20,826 --> 00:26:22,293
[ Saul ]
Jonathan!

341
00:26:24,696 --> 00:26:26,095
[ Groans ]

342
00:26:26,164 --> 00:26:29,065
Jonathan!

343
00:26:33,505 --> 00:26:35,598
Jonathan. Jonathan.

344
00:26:36,842 --> 00:26:39,310
[ Crying ]
Oh, my son!

345
00:26:39,378 --> 00:26:42,176
Oh, why?

346
00:26:47,619 --> 00:26:49,086
[ Kisses ]

347
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:09,701
Dear God.

348
00:27:12,110 --> 00:27:14,044
Were my sins so great...

349
00:27:15,147 --> 00:27:17,172
all of lsrael must suffer?

350
00:27:38,136 --> 00:27:39,899
[ Sword Plunges ]

351
00:27:43,775 --> 00:27:44,969
[ Groans ]

352
00:27:58,623 --> 00:28:00,113
Hyah! Hyah!

353
00:28:16,074 --> 00:28:17,666
A crushing victory...

354
00:28:19,611 --> 00:28:21,238
for the Philistines.

355
00:28:28,253 --> 00:28:29,743
And Saul?

356
00:28:33,158 --> 00:28:35,592
Dead.
[ Laughing ]

357
00:28:40,332 --> 00:28:43,529
You think the death
of God's anointed is a trivial thing?

358
00:28:45,103 --> 00:28:46,934
What of Jonathan?

359
00:28:48,974 --> 00:28:50,874
Captured?

360
00:28:54,713 --> 00:28:56,203
Get rid of him!

361
00:29:10,662 --> 00:29:12,823
How are the mighty fallen.

362
00:29:22,107 --> 00:29:23,904
We can go home.

363
00:29:29,514 --> 00:29:31,880
The people will look to you now...

364
00:29:31,950 --> 00:29:34,578
to defend them, unite them.

365
00:29:40,125 --> 00:29:42,025
Our time has come.

366
00:29:47,666 --> 00:29:49,861
Yes, my king.

367
00:29:59,344 --> 00:30:01,107
King David.

368
00:30:03,415 --> 00:30:05,713
[ Narrator ]
Davld gathers followers.

369
00:30:05,784 --> 00:30:09,845
But to unlte Israel
he needs a capltal clty.

370
00:30:10,555 --> 00:30:12,216
Jerusalem.

371
00:30:12,290 --> 00:30:14,121
Our new home.

372
00:30:16,528 --> 00:30:18,496
Now we just need to find a way in.

373
00:30:19,464 --> 00:30:21,398
How do we do that?

374
00:30:22,567 --> 00:30:24,159
There is one way.

375
00:30:25,170 --> 00:30:28,071
- We wait till nightfall.
- [ Whinnies ]

376
00:30:32,110 --> 00:30:34,101
[ Men Coughing ]

377
00:31:28,033 --> 00:31:30,024
[ Uriah ]
What do we do now?

378
00:31:32,137 --> 00:31:33,399
Here.

379
00:31:47,185 --> 00:31:49,176
[ Gasping ]

380
00:32:27,726 --> 00:32:30,820
[ Men Chattering, Laughing ]

381
00:32:41,339 --> 00:32:43,068
[ Chattering, Laughing Continue ]

382
00:32:43,141 --> 00:32:45,905
...what happened to Saul!
[ Laughing ]

383
00:32:59,858 --> 00:33:02,793
[ Panting ]
For lsrael.

384
00:33:04,129 --> 00:33:05,960
- Look out!
- To arms!

385
00:33:16,608 --> 00:33:17,575
Uriah!

386
00:33:37,228 --> 00:33:39,423
lsrael!

387
00:33:39,497 --> 00:33:41,590
[ Men Cheering, Shouting ]

388
00:33:56,214 --> 00:33:58,808
- ^^ [ Drumming ]
- [ Cheering ]

389
00:34:01,853 --> 00:34:05,914
[ Narrator ]
Jerusalem is now Davld 's clty...

390
00:34:05,990 --> 00:34:09,050
a new center of power
for the Israelites...

391
00:34:10,462 --> 00:34:14,455
and a home for the ultimate symboI
of their bond wlth God.

392
00:34:14,532 --> 00:34:16,830
The Ark of the Covenant!

393
00:34:16,901 --> 00:34:18,766
[ Cheering ]

394
00:34:18,837 --> 00:34:21,271
- [ Crowd Chanting, Singing ]
- ^^ [ Drumming ]

395
00:34:32,150 --> 00:34:34,516
Your wife's far too pretty for you,
my friend.

396
00:34:34,586 --> 00:34:35,985
- You're right.
- [ Laughs ]

397
00:34:36,054 --> 00:34:37,817
- Majesty.
- Come.

398
00:34:37,889 --> 00:34:40,414
- You don't mind, Uriah.
- l mind.

399
00:35:33,445 --> 00:35:35,845
Now God is truly with me.

400
00:35:39,184 --> 00:35:41,880
[ Birds Chirping, Calling ]

401
00:36:11,282 --> 00:36:12,977
Your Majesty.

402
00:36:13,485 --> 00:36:15,544
Ah. Prophet.

403
00:36:20,892 --> 00:36:22,382
Look.

404
00:36:22,460 --> 00:36:24,655
My temple.

405
00:36:24,729 --> 00:36:26,094
For the Ark.

406
00:36:26,164 --> 00:36:27,791
For the Lord.

407
00:36:27,866 --> 00:36:29,925
The world's never seen anything like it.

408
00:36:30,001 --> 00:36:32,060
The Lord came to me last night.

409
00:36:32,136 --> 00:36:34,070
He's pleased with our work?

410
00:36:34,138 --> 00:36:37,665
The Lord told me the House of David
will rule lsrael forever.

411
00:36:39,010 --> 00:36:40,705
We are blessed.

412
00:36:40,778 --> 00:36:43,406
Your son will be king.

413
00:36:43,481 --> 00:36:46,006
Your son will build the temple.

414
00:36:47,852 --> 00:36:49,080
My temple.

415
00:36:49,153 --> 00:36:51,383
God's temple.

416
00:36:53,758 --> 00:36:55,248
God's temple.

417
00:36:56,928 --> 00:36:58,862
A kingdom forever.

418
00:37:00,365 --> 00:37:02,196
Thank you, Nathan.

419
00:37:05,970 --> 00:37:07,460
[ Woman Laughs ]

420
00:37:25,590 --> 00:37:27,217
[ Man ]
Your Majesty.

421
00:37:28,726 --> 00:37:30,591
As you requested.

422
00:37:31,563 --> 00:37:33,190
Leave us.

423
00:37:37,669 --> 00:37:39,569
Bathsheba.

424
00:37:39,637 --> 00:37:40,831
Majesty.

425
00:37:41,673 --> 00:37:43,300
David.

426
00:37:43,374 --> 00:37:45,399
ls there news of my husband?

427
00:37:46,811 --> 00:37:48,574
No.

428
00:37:48,646 --> 00:37:51,376
No, nothing like that.
He's safe enough, l believe...

429
00:37:51,449 --> 00:37:54,475
although he is far away.

430
00:37:55,453 --> 00:37:57,216
Fighting the enemy.

431
00:37:58,022 --> 00:37:59,853
But you didn't go.

432
00:37:59,924 --> 00:38:01,687
No need.

433
00:38:01,759 --> 00:38:04,751
Not with men like Uriah to do it for me.

434
00:38:08,967 --> 00:38:11,265
l am loyal to my husband.

435
00:38:26,284 --> 00:38:28,218
What about your king?

436
00:38:39,564 --> 00:38:41,054
This is wrong.

437
00:38:52,477 --> 00:38:54,468
No one need know.

438
00:39:05,356 --> 00:39:07,756
[ Narrator ]
Bathsheba becomes pregnant.

439
00:39:08,860 --> 00:39:12,318
God's chosen king breaks his commandments.

440
00:39:13,798 --> 00:39:16,494
Uriah, my friend. Welcome.

441
00:39:20,004 --> 00:39:21,995
You sent for me, Majesty.

442
00:39:25,376 --> 00:39:27,606
How's the war going?

443
00:39:27,679 --> 00:39:29,738
Well. Very well.

444
00:39:33,284 --> 00:39:35,752
And your commander, Joab,
all is well with him?

445
00:39:35,820 --> 00:39:37,720
All is well.

446
00:39:37,789 --> 00:39:39,450
Your fellow soldiers?

447
00:39:39,524 --> 00:39:41,549
They fight well.

448
00:39:41,626 --> 00:39:44,060
Excellent.

449
00:39:44,128 --> 00:39:46,426
Well, you can give me
a fuller report in the morning.

450
00:39:46,497 --> 00:39:48,488
l'm sure for now
you'd rather be with your wife.

451
00:39:48,566 --> 00:39:49,794
[ Laughs ]

452
00:39:49,867 --> 00:39:53,200
- l cannot stay with my wife.
- Of course you can.

453
00:39:54,439 --> 00:39:57,374
While my men are camped in open country...

454
00:39:57,442 --> 00:39:59,467
fighting the enemy?

455
00:40:00,611 --> 00:40:02,806
This is a holy war.

456
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:06,976
How could l go to my home
and spend the night with my wife?

457
00:40:07,051 --> 00:40:09,645
That does you credit, Uriah.

458
00:40:09,721 --> 00:40:11,746
But, man to man...

459
00:40:11,823 --> 00:40:13,313
who's to know?

460
00:40:15,059 --> 00:40:16,788
l will know.

461
00:40:21,099 --> 00:40:22,726
Good man.

462
00:40:23,868 --> 00:40:25,563
Then let's drink.

463
00:40:26,971 --> 00:40:28,370
Wine!

464
00:40:47,024 --> 00:40:50,653
[ Narrator ] Davld cannot force Urlah
to sleep wlth Bathsheba.

465
00:40:52,497 --> 00:40:55,261
So he finds another way...

466
00:40:55,333 --> 00:40:57,426
to conceal his adultery.

467
00:41:17,622 --> 00:41:21,023
[ Davld 's Voice ]
Commander Joab, I order you to send Urlah...

468
00:41:21,092 --> 00:41:23,253
to where the fighting is flercest...

469
00:41:23,327 --> 00:41:26,091
and abandon him there to dle .

470
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:57,551
We've been richly blessed.

471
00:41:59,664 --> 00:42:02,428
You think you can just
sweep what you've done under the carpet?

472
00:42:03,801 --> 00:42:07,202
You took everything from your most
loyal servant, Uriah.

473
00:42:07,271 --> 00:42:09,739
- He deserved your respect.
- l did respect him.

474
00:42:09,807 --> 00:42:11,274
Really?

475
00:42:11,342 --> 00:42:14,175
- You took his wife, then you took his life.
- Prophet!

476
00:42:14,245 --> 00:42:17,214
You think God doesn't see everything?

477
00:42:19,083 --> 00:42:21,074
The Lord has spoken to me.

478
00:42:21,152 --> 00:42:24,121
He will bring disaster on your house...

479
00:42:24,188 --> 00:42:26,713
for the contempt you have shown the Lord.

480
00:42:33,631 --> 00:42:35,963
- No.
- No!

481
00:42:36,033 --> 00:42:38,228
He will take your son.

482
00:42:42,506 --> 00:42:43,973
- [ Baby Cries ]
- We shall see.

483
00:42:44,909 --> 00:42:47,878
[ Crying Continues ]

484
00:42:59,824 --> 00:43:02,156
Anything, Lord.

485
00:43:03,561 --> 00:43:05,791
Please spare my child.

486
00:43:10,668 --> 00:43:12,295
Tell me.

487
00:43:14,805 --> 00:43:16,932
Tell me what to do.

488
00:43:25,483 --> 00:43:26,848
[ Sobs ]

489
00:43:26,918 --> 00:43:28,180
Oh.

490
00:43:29,520 --> 00:43:31,920
[ Sobbing ]

491
00:43:31,989 --> 00:43:35,447
First my husband, now my son.

492
00:43:37,461 --> 00:43:39,122
We are cursed.

493
00:43:41,799 --> 00:43:43,733
But l was anointed.

494
00:43:45,069 --> 00:43:46,627
God blessed me.

495
00:43:46,704 --> 00:43:48,672
A king is never above his god.

496
00:43:49,974 --> 00:43:52,272
You were supposed to rule in his name,
not your own.

497
00:43:52,343 --> 00:43:54,038
We're finished.

498
00:43:55,112 --> 00:43:57,706
Everyone will see that God has left us.

499
00:44:05,256 --> 00:44:06,814
Prophet.

500
00:44:08,192 --> 00:44:11,889
Even though you are weak,
he loves you, David.

501
00:44:13,331 --> 00:44:16,494
You have forged God's nation on earth.

502
00:44:19,770 --> 00:44:21,761
Take comfort in each other.

503
00:44:22,940 --> 00:44:24,931
You will have another son.

504
00:44:33,217 --> 00:44:35,412
[ All Laughing ]

505
00:44:35,486 --> 00:44:38,080
[ Laughing ]

506
00:44:41,425 --> 00:44:43,416
[ Laughing ]

507
00:44:44,929 --> 00:44:46,760
Be careful, Solomon.

508
00:44:46,831 --> 00:44:47,991
Let him play.

509
00:44:48,833 --> 00:44:50,664
lt's the house of the Lord.

510
00:44:52,269 --> 00:44:54,533
One day, he'll have to build it.

511
00:44:56,273 --> 00:44:59,572
[ Narrator ]
Solomon will build God's temple .

512
00:44:59,643 --> 00:45:01,474
But like his father...

513
00:45:01,545 --> 00:45:05,379
he will find lt impossible
to obey God's commandments.

514
00:45:07,952 --> 00:45:10,216
Next time on The Bible.

515
00:45:10,287 --> 00:45:11,879
[ Chanting ]
Nebuchadnezzar! Nebuchadnezzar!

516
00:45:11,956 --> 00:45:15,050
[ Man ]
God is bringing disaster from Babylon!

517
00:45:15,126 --> 00:45:16,616
[ Chanting ]
Nebuchadnezzar!

518
00:45:16,694 --> 00:45:18,218
We move!

519
00:45:18,295 --> 00:45:20,195
Jerusalem!

520
00:45:20,264 --> 00:45:23,859
[ Shouting ]

521
00:45:26,303 --> 00:45:30,137
Will you not speak for us
in our hour of need?

522
00:45:31,242 --> 00:45:32,800
[ Man ]
Look out there.

523
00:45:33,677 --> 00:45:35,577
You're too late.

524
00:45:36,647 --> 00:45:38,376
- lt begins.
- [ Thunder Rumbling ]

525
00:45:40,384 --> 00:45:44,377
Submit to King Nebuchadnezzar.
Bow your head.

526
00:45:52,663 --> 00:45:56,099
And whatever is left of Jerusalem,
help yourselves!

527
00:45:58,069 --> 00:46:00,299
This way, Daniel.

528
00:46:00,371 --> 00:46:01,668
[ Screaming ]

529
00:46:09,380 --> 00:46:11,439
[ Man ]
WilI we ever return to Jerusalem?

530
00:46:11,515 --> 00:46:13,847
Jeremiah promised that one day we would.

531
00:46:13,918 --> 00:46:16,011
[ Man ]
In the meantime, what do we do-

532
00:46:16,087 --> 00:46:18,078
just bow our heads and serve this monster?

533
00:46:18,155 --> 00:46:20,680
l will make them bow.

534
00:46:20,758 --> 00:46:22,248
Bring me fire!

535
00:46:22,326 --> 00:46:24,794
Lord! Save me!

536
00:46:24,862 --> 00:46:26,796
[ Screaming ]

537
00:46:33,070 --> 00:46:36,233
[ Danlel ] Cyrus will set us free
lf the prophecy is right.

538
00:46:36,307 --> 00:46:37,831
[ Cyrus ]
I cannot go back on my word.

539
00:46:37,908 --> 00:46:40,172
l promised them freedom to worship.

540
00:46:40,244 --> 00:46:42,144
lt is merely a test of their loyalty.

541
00:46:42,213 --> 00:46:44,613
lt's a trap for all of us.
They want us dead.

542
00:46:44,682 --> 00:46:47,708
[ Roaring ]

543
00:46:47,785 --> 00:46:51,152
[ Man ] There is one to come
who will baptize wlth fire.

544
00:46:51,222 --> 00:46:53,884
l'm just a voice in the wilderness,
preparing the way for the-

545
00:46:56,560 --> 00:46:57,720
[ Man ]
Lord.

546
00:46:57,795 --> 00:47:00,195
